The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, February 12, 2004 				 Father kills kids, self
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Ahmedabad, Feb. 11: A 35-year-old man unable to bear the humiliation of his wife eloping with her lover killed his two minor children and committed suicide in Bharuch district today.																								The incident is a chilling follow-up to Thursdays deaths, when Salim Ghulam Hussain Sheikh, also a resident of Bharuch district, threw his five daughters into the Narmada.																								Natwar Patel, 35, hanged himself early this morning after hanging daughter Heena, 9, and son Vipin, 8, at his father-in-laws house at Kalak village in Jambusar taluka, Bharuch district superintendent of police Amarsinh Vasava said																								Natwar, who lives in a village in Vadodara district, is believed to have been driven to the extreme step after his wife Sumitra, 31, eloped with Arvind Jethawal.																								On February 1, Natwar came to his father-in-law Rasik Patels house, at which Sumitra had been staying of late, to settle matters. He wanted Rasik and the village elders to tell Sumitra not to ruin their marriage. But even as the panchayat tried to convince Sumitra to sever ties with Arvind, a resident of Vadodara, she eloped with him yesterday.																								Jolted, the cuckolded Natwar hanged his children and himself, leaving behind a suicide note. He said he was taking the extreme step because he could not bear the disgrace and humiliation caused by the elopement. 
